				<!-- About Me -->
					<section id="about" class="three">
						<div="container">
							<header>
								<h2>About Me</h2>
							</header>
							<div align="middle">
								<a class="image featured"><img src="images/pic_mod.jpg" alt="" /></a>
							</div>
							<div align="middle"><p align="center">
<b>The name:</b> Luis Filipe Dias.<br>
<b>The degree:</b> Master in Electronics and Telecommunications, by the <b>University of Aveiro</b>.<br>	
<b>The main</b> professional interests:
<ul>
	<li><b>Radio-Frequency Electronics:</b> <b>Antennas</b> and <b>Energy Harvesting Systems</b>, since my thesis consisted on the study and development of efficient <b>Energy Harvesting Circuits</b> for generation of <b>no-cost illumination</b> (you can find more information here).</li><br>
	<li><b>Hardware Engineering:</b> 1.5 years working as a <b>Hardware Engineer</b>, with cutting edge-hardware for fiber optics, sharpened my interest on this area of technology. Here are some things I learned:
		<ul>
       		<li>To integrate a multidisciplinary team, responsible for the Firmware integration of long-haul optical equipments;</li><br>
                <li>- To Execute and analyse of Hardware validation tests (Surge testing, EMC, Temperature tests, Worst-Case power consumption and others);</li><br>
                <li>- To handle testing, measurement and characterization equipments for optical and high-frequency electrical interfaces (Optical Traffic Analysers/Generators, High-Frequency Oscilloscopes, Variable Optical Attenuators, etc.);</li><br>
                <li>- To comprehend and apply distinct standards/protocols, both internal and internationally regulated (ANSI, ITU-T, IEEE, ETSI,...)</li><br>
      </ul></li>
	<li><b>-> Embedded Systems Engineering:</b> my latest challenge, is about bridging from the hardware into the low level drivers, and then up the stack into the higher levels of the application. It has been a challenging but really worthwhile learning experience. Some of the things I do:
		<ul>
			<li>C - lot!</li>
			<li>Develop embedded software for different chip-sets, architectures and hardware sets;</li>
			<li>Work on different levels of the SW stack (from the device-drivers to the application);</li>
			<li>Comprehend and modify Buildsystems (cmake, kbuild, ...);</li>
			<li>Comprehend the HW layer and the link with the low-level SW;</li>
			<li>Debugg the HW layer;</li>
			<li>Prepare setups for SW validation tests;</li>
			<li>Understande and enforce technical specifications;</li>
		</ul>
</ul>
Other non-related personal interests involve travelling, gastronomy, cinema, mountain biking, squash or table tennis.<br>
If you wish to <b>contact me</b> please refer to the contacts section the website.<br>
						</p></div>
					</section>
			
